friend of Ava DuVernay's.

00:23:35.290 --> 00:23:39.700
I do not use that term lightly
because over the years,

00:23:39.700 --> 00:23:43.240
I have chosen my
friends carefully.

00:23:43.240 --> 00:23:47.140
And I have had a
best friend, Gayle,

00:23:47.140 --> 00:23:51.580
who's been my best friend
since we were 21 and 22.

00:23:51.580 --> 00:23:53.695
I actively sought
another friend.

00:23:53.695 --> 00:23:56.290
[LAUGHTER]

00:23:56.290 --> 00:23:57.880
Because Gayle is busy a lot.

00:23:57.880 --> 00:23:59.590
[LAUGHTER]

00:23:59.590 --> 00:24:02.170
And I actively sought
another friend.

00:24:02.170 --> 00:24:06.460
So someone had shown
me a DVD of Ava's work

00:24:06.460 --> 00:24:09.190
for another movie called
"The Middle of Nowhere".

00:24:09.190 --> 00:24:13.220
And I liked the movie, and
then I went and looked up--

00:24:13.220 --> 00:24:14.140
Googled her.

00:24:14.140 --> 00:24:16.060
I Googled her.

00:24:16.060 --> 00:24:17.895
Hello, Google, I Googled her.

00:24:17.895 --> 00:24:21.080
[CHEERING]

00:24:21.080 --> 00:24:27.230
And there I saw this
essence of someone

00:24:27.230 --> 00:24:28.470
who I wanted to be my friend.

00:24:28.470 --> 00:24:31.670
First of all, she was
a girl with glasses.

00:24:31.670 --> 00:24:33.380
She looked like me,
and I thought, gee

00:24:33.380 --> 00:24:34.380
I want to be her friend.

00:24:34.380 --> 00:24:37.550
So I actively sought
to create an event

00:24:37.550 --> 00:24:42.240
so that she could
come to my house

00:24:42.240 --> 00:24:43.730
so that she would be my friend.

00:24:43.730 --> 00:24:47.040
So that worked.

00:24:47.040 --> 00:24:50.720
And then, I, as a
friend, when you

00:24:50.720 --> 00:24:53.450
have a friend that you
love and you care about,

00:24:53.450 --> 00:24:56.222
you want to do everything you
can to support your friends.

00:24:56.222 --> 00:24:57.680
That's the kind of
friend you want.

00:24:57.680 --> 00:25:01.970
You want a friend that
wants for you, as much

00:25:01.970 --> 00:25:05.460
as you want something,
they want it even more.

00:25:05.460 --> 00:25:09.590
So I wanted to support my
friend in doing this film.

00:25:09.590 --> 00:25:13.391
So I said, I'm going to
come to New Zealand, girl.

00:25:13.391 --> 00:25:16.320
And I'm going watch you
work and say, action.

00:25:16.320 --> 00:25:19.640
And I just want to be there
when you tell all those people

00:25:19.640 --> 00:25:22.204
action and cut.

00:25:22.204 --> 00:25:24.620
And I kept saying it, oh, I'm
coming to New Zealand, girl.

00:25:24.620 --> 00:25:25.703
I'm coming to New Zealand.

00:25:25.703 --> 00:25:28.340
And she said, if you're
really going to do that, would

00:25:28.340 --> 00:25:33.140
you consider reading this part.

00:25:33.140 --> 00:25:37.190
And I said, yeah,
girl, I'll do that.

00:25:37.190 --> 00:25:39.320
So that's actually
how it happened.

00:25:39.320 --> 00:25:41.240
Because I was seeking
her as a friend,

00:25:41.240 --> 00:25:43.970
I saw something in her
essence that has turned out

00:25:43.970 --> 00:25:45.740
to be even more profound.

00:25:45.740 --> 00:25:48.290
So then I read
this role, and it's

00:25:48.290 --> 00:25:50.840
like everything I could
imagine for myself.

00:25:50.840 --> 00:25:54.050
So I had a wonderful
mother, friend, teacher,

00:25:54.050 --> 00:25:55.931
mentor named Maya Angelou.

00:25:55.931 --> 00:25:56.930
Do you know who that is?

00:25:56.930 --> 00:25:58.910
[APPLAUSE]

00:25:59.900 --> 00:26:02.520
So I read her book when
I was about your age,

00:26:02.520 --> 00:26:06.260
and then I ended up
becoming her daughter.

00:26:06.260 --> 00:26:10.100
And so she was my spiritual
guide, mentor, teacher.

00:26:10.100 --> 00:26:14.840
And I modeled this character,
Mrs. Which, from Maya Angelou

00:26:14.840 --> 00:26:19.370
and from the Wizard of
Oz, Glinda the Good Witch.

00:26:19.370 --> 00:26:20.840
So when Glinda the
Good Witch says,

00:26:20.840 --> 00:26:22.340
you've always had
the power, I think

00:26:22.340 --> 00:26:23.881
that's one of the
greatest teachings.

00:26:23.881 --> 00:26:26.960
So to be able to have
Maya Angelou and Glinda

00:26:26.960 --> 00:26:30.410
the Good Witch and then a
bit of my own self in there.

00:26:30.410 --> 00:26:32.960
Because in the very
beginning, when

00:26:32.960 --> 00:26:35.750
Mrs. Which first shows up at
the beginning of the film,

00:26:35.750 --> 00:26:40.910
and she says to Meg,
all you have to do

00:26:40.910 --> 00:26:45.980
is find the right frequency
and have faith in who you are,

00:26:45.980 --> 00:26:49.740
that is my true philosophy
for how you live your life.

00:26:49.740 --> 00:26:53.170
And if I had any advice to give
to you all today, that is it.

00:26:53.170 --> 00:26:56.270
It starts at the
beginning of the movie.

00:26:56.270 --> 00:26:59.900
All you have to do is
find the right frequency.

00:26:59.900 --> 00:27:05.060
Because everybody has their own
frequency that is just yours.

00:27:05.060 --> 00:27:07.220
And when you can
ride that frequency,

00:27:07.220 --> 00:27:11.990
find the flow that is for
you and have faith in that,

00:27:11.990 --> 00:27:14.069
unimaginable things
become possible for you.

00:27:14.069 --> 00:27:15.360
So that's why I love the movie.

00:27:15.360 --> 00:27:17.162
For that message and
for my friend, Ava.

00:27:17.162 --> 00:27:18.620
EILEEN NAUGHTON:
Beautiful message.

00:27:18.620 --> 00:27:21.650
And it's a beautiful lesson
for us here today, and I think,

00:27:21.650 --> 00:27:25.670
Reese, welcome, you have found
your right frequency lately.

00:27:25.670 --> 00:27:26.660
It's remarkable.

